Fig. 
<quantity id="4CD19B0DFFC6FFDAF4F3FE1A3C28C2A6" box="[757,787,404,429]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="238" unit="m" value="26.0">26</quantity>
</figureCitation>
m). It appears that the collection sketch is more accurate. Importantly, since the cuculli were broken off the 
<typeStatus id="5492884AFFC6FFDAF4C8FE393C0BC2DB" box="[718,816,439,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">holotype</typeStatus>
genitalia mount, both of these sketches made from the 
<typeStatus id="5492884AFFC6FFDAF691FE523FC2C2FE" box="[151,249,476,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">holotype</typeStatus>
(TL: 
<collectingCountry id="F33E7678FFC6FFDAF73BFE523EDCC2FE" box="[317,487,476,501]" name="French Guiana" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, the sole [para] 
<typeStatus id="5492884AFFC6FFDAF492FE533DFDC2FE" box="[660,710,477,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">type</typeStatus>
was not dissected, see 
<figureCitation id="13122A6DFFC6FFDAF5D7FE523B63C2FF" box="[977,1112,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1731,1753]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,193,1707]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[152,1435,193,1709]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 16. Type specimens of Clito from the C. littera group. 9 – 10. C. littera lectotype, designated here, &quot; Brasil &quot;, P. Mabille collection 1923, R. Oberthür Coll., Brit. Mus. 1927 - 3, specimen No. BMNH (E)  982948 (genitalia Fig. 26 a, g); 11 – 12. C. anda [holo] type, French Guiana, Collect. C. Bar, R. Oberthür Coll., Brit. Mus. 1931 - 136, specimen No. BMNH (E)  982947; (genitalia Fig. 26 m, n, o); 13 – 14. C. anda [para] type, French Guiana: Cayenne, R. Oberthür Coll., Brit. Mus. 1931 - 136, specimen No. BMNH (E)  1054238; 15 – 16. C. nebulosa holotype, Bolivia, Rio Songo, 750 m, Coll. Fassl (genitalia Fig. 26 d). All specimens are males. Dorsal and ventral surfaces are shown on odd- and even-numbered figures, respectively. Labels are shown in-line with the specimen images. Labels are reduced 2.5 times compared to specimens: small scale bar below C. littera labels refers to labels, and larger scale bars refer to specimens. 15 – 16 is in SMF collection and is photographed by Ernst Brockmann, other specimens are in BMNH collection and images are copyright (©) Trustees of the Natural History Museum, London (used with permission)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252287/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">
Figs. 
<number id="3DE124CFFFC6FFDAF217FE523B63C2FF" box="[1041,1112,476,500]" pageId="7" pageNumber="238" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13–14</number>
</figureCitation>
) and Austin drawing from a Rondônia specimen show the distal bulge of the cucullus in 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6BFFC6FFDAF54FFD8E3C98C113" box="[841,931,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Clito" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anda">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFAFFC6FFDAF54FFD8E3C98C113" box="[841,931,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">C. anda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, thus setting this species apart from both 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6BFFC6FFDAF384FD8E3FE0C136" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Telemiades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="littera">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFAFFC6FFDAF384FD8E3FE0C136" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">C. littera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6BFFC6FFDAF717FDAB3EADC136" authority="Butler, 1870" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1870" box="[273,406,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hydraenomia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nebulosa">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFAFFC6FFDAF717FDAB3EADC136" box="[273,406,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">C. nebulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the two species without this distal expansion and the cucullus narrowing gradually towards the dorsally pointed tip. After Evan's work, two more 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6BFFC6FFDAF512FDC93C77C16B" box="[788,844,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Clito" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFAFFC6FFDAF512FDC93C77C16B" box="[788,844,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">Clito</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with apparent phylogenetic affinities to 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D6BFFC6FFDAF384FDC63FE0C18E" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Telemiades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="littera">
<emphasis id="B95DEAFAFFC6FFDAF384FDC63FE0C18E" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="238">C. littera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been discovered.
